<AdminPage ID="x62590" Name="Travel Forms" Layout="admin_office_home.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Travel Forms</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Travel Forms</Abstract><MainMesgTop type="boolean" label="Enable to move &quot;Main Message&quot; to top of page" readonly="false" required="false" hidden="false">false</MainMesgTop><IntroCopy type="dhtml" label="Main Message" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<dl style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;"><dt><a href="https://web.byui.edu/travel/ta" title="Travel Application"><strong>Travel Application/Authorization/Reconciliation</strong></a></dt><dd style="padding-left: 10px;">This portal will provide you with all the forms and information you need:</dd><dd style="padding-left: 30px;">As an employee - to apply for travel and reconcile completed applications</dd><dd style="padding-left: 30px;">As a supervisor - to authorize Travel Applications made by employees</dd><br /><dt><a href="http://www.byui.edu/travel/Forms/TrvlProfileWarnng.htm" title="Traveler Profile"><strong>Traveler Profile</strong></a></dt><dd style="padding-left: 10px;">Who are you? This is your profile that will be used as you book your travel</dd><br /><dt><strong><a class="extLink" href="http://www.byui.edu/Documents/financial-services/Tour_GroupAuthorization.PDF" title="Authorization Form" target="_blank">Overnight Student Travel Authorizaion Form</a></strong></dt><dd style="padding-left: 10px;">Before traveling in a group, you need to fill out this Overnight Authorization Form.<br /></dd><dt><a href="Documents/financial-services/TourGroupChcklist.pdf" title="Group Travel Checklist" target="_blank"><strong>Group Travel Checklist</strong></a></dt><dd style="padding-left: 10px;">Group Leaders/Directors should complete this checklist as they prepare for domestic and international student trips</dd><br /><dt><a href="Documents/financial-services/ActivityWaiver.pdf" title="Waiver for Student Travel and Activities" target="_blank"><strong>Waiver for Student Travel and Activities</strong></a></dt><dd style="padding-left: 10px;">This waiver should be used for all non-mandatory student tours and travel or for mandatory travel if the students opt to make their own travel arrangements. An employee should complete the top portion paying special attention to the specific risks associated with that activity. Signed waivers should be retained two (2) years plus the current year unless an incident occurs then they should be retained five (5) years plus the current year.</dd><br /><dt><a href="http://web.byui.edu/guesttravel" title="Guest Travel Request"><strong>Guest Travel Request</strong></a></dt><dd style="padding-left: 10px;">If you've got a guest traveling to the University (speaker, performer, etc.), you need to fill out this online form</dd><br /><dt><a href="x35093.xml#travel_reimbursements" title="Who to Call"><strong>Who to Call</strong></a></dt><dd style="padding-left: 10px;">Need more information or help planning your next trip? Give us a call and we'll lend you a hand!</dd></dl>
